phase-1 / Auth & Identity Agent

WHAT I DID
- Built the auth screens under app/(auth)/: sign-up (screen 1) with email +
  password, display name, mode select (seeker/companion), and guidelines
  acceptance; login; forgot-password; reset-password; the Supabase OAuth
  callback handler; a check-email landing for confirmation flows; and a
  POST /logout route. Mobile-first styling via styles.module.css.
- Wired Supabase Auth session handling: middleware.ts refreshes the
  session cookie on every request; lib/auth/session.ts exposes
  getSessionUser / requireSessionUser / requireMode for server code; the
  client AuthProvider (lib/auth/context.tsx) is mounted in the root
  layout so client components can read the session app-wide.
- Implemented the one-account-two-modes model: sign-up captures both
  flags, the public.users mirror row is upserted via the admin client,
  app/(auth)/mode/ exposes a mode-switcher (server action calls
  updateUserModes which enforces the "at least one mode" invariant
  client-side AND defers to the schema check constraint).
- Built the verification flow:
  - Seeker (lighter): email confirmation (Supabase Auth) + guidelines
    acceptance auto-promote users.seeker_verification_status to
    'verified' via reconcileSeekerVerification (called from sign-up,
    login, callback, and the accept-guidelines route).
  - Companion (stronger): app/(auth)/verify/companion submits legal
    name + an identity document. Document goes to a private
    'verification' Storage bucket; companion_profiles.verification_status
    moves to 'pending'. Admin-side transition to 'verified' is
    intentionally out-of-scope (flagged below). RLS continues to enforce
    that unverified companions are non-discoverable/non-bookable - core
    product rule #9.
- Implemented profile photo upload (lib/auth/storage.ts) with
  server-side MIME + size validation, idempotent bucket provisioning,
  and writeback of users.avatar_path. The AvatarUploader component is
  surfaced in the verification hub.
- Reflected auth state app-wide by wrapping children in <AuthProvider>
  inside app/layout.tsx (resolves the initial session server-side).

WHAT I COULD NOT DO
- Could not actually run the dev server end-to-end - no Supabase
  project is provisioned (Supabase URLs/keys are blank in .env.local
  beyond placeholders). Type-check passes for all auth code; runtime
  verification requires a live project.
- Did not move companion_profiles.verification_status to 'verified' -
  that requires the admin/review path (and ideally a third-party
  identity provider like Stripe Identity or Persona). Out of scope for
  Phase 1; the submission flow halts at 'pending'.
- Did not introduce a Postgres trigger to mirror auth.users into
  public.users automatically - that would be a Database-agent change.
  The mirror row is created via the admin client from server actions
  instead.
- Did not address the pre-existing type-check failure in
  lib/supabase/server.ts (cookies() became async in Next 16). The
  Foundations agent owns that file; flagged under MANUAL CHECKPOINTS.

INTERFACES PUBLISHED
- Server (import from '@/lib/auth/session'):
    getSessionUser(): Promise<SessionUser | null>
    requireSessionUser(redirectTo?: string): Promise<SessionUser>
    requireMode(mode: 'seeker' | 'companion'): Promise<SessionUser>
    type SessionUser { id, email, emailConfirmed, profile: UserRow|null }
- Client (import from '@/lib/auth'):
    <AuthProvider initialSession={Session|null}>
    useAuth(): { session, isLoading, signOut() }
- Server (import from '@/lib/auth/profile'):
    createUserMirrorRow(input)
    updateUserModes({ isSeeker, isCompanion })
    acceptGuidelines()
- Server (import from '@/lib/auth/verification'):
    submitCompanionVerification({ legalName, documentPath })
    reconcileSeekerVerification(userId)
- Server (import from '@/lib/auth/storage'):
    uploadAvatar(blob), uploadVerificationDocument(blob),
    avatarPublicUrl(path),
    constants AVATAR_BUCKET = 'avatars', VERIFICATION_BUCKET = 'verification'
- HTTP surface (Auth & Identity owned):
    GET  /sign-up, /login, /forgot-password, /reset-password,
         /check-email, /verify, /verify/companion, /mode
    POST /logout
    POST /verify/accept-guidelines
    GET  /callback?code=...&next=... (Supabase email/PKCE exchange)

MANUAL CHECKPOINTS
- Storage buckets: lib/auth/storage.ts auto-creates 'avatars' (public)
  and 'verification' (private) buckets via the service role on first
  upload, but Storage RLS policies for these buckets should be
  configured by the Database/Foundations agent (e.g. restrict 'avatars'
  writes to the owning user's path prefix; restrict 'verification'
  reads to admins). Auto-creation also depends on
  SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY being set.
- Email confirmation / redirect URLs: the Supabase project Auth
  settings need the app URL added to the allow-list
  (NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL), and the email templates should point to
  /callback?code={code}&next=... for sign-up and
  /callback?code={code}&next=/reset-password for password reset.
  Configured in the Supabase dashboard - I did not modify project
  config.
- Identity verification provider: companion verification currently
  ends at 'pending' and an admin must move the row to 'verified' (or
  'rejected'). Wiring this to a real ID-check vendor (Stripe Identity,
  Persona, Veriff) is a follow-up product decision - flagging it for
  the Orchestrator and Trust & Safety review.
- Pre-existing type-check failures owned by Foundations:
    lib/supabase/server.ts uses synchronous `cookies()`, which became
    async in Next 16 (installed version is 16.2.6, package.json pins
    14.2.18 - the lockfile is ahead). The auth code is unaffected at
    runtime, but `npm run type-check` will report 3 errors against
    that file until Foundations rewrites the cookie adapter as async.
- Pre-existing lint failure owned by Foundations:
    `next lint` was removed in Next 15+; `npm run lint` now errors
    out with "Invalid project directory provided". Needs to switch to
    `eslint .` or the new lint integration.
- Database type regeneration (Database agent): the hand-authored
  `Database` shape in lib/types/database.ts no longer satisfies
  supabase-js 2.105's `GenericSchema` constraints
  (`Views: Record<string, never>` collapses every table to `never` in
  query inference). The auth module uses local typed adapters
  (lib/auth/db.ts) and projects results into the published Row types
  to work around this. Removing the adapters is a one-line change
  once Foundations regenerates the type via `supabase gen types
  typescript`.
